article.linkText: DeCosey gives Temple a 63-61 win over Central Florida
article.story: PHILADELPHIA -- Quenton DeCosey scored 16 points, including the game-winning jumper with 3.1 seconds left, and Temple edged Central Florida 63-61 on Saturday. Central Florida tied the game when Daiquan Walker made two of three free throws with a minute left. DeCosey fired an airball 3 near the end of the shot clock but UCF lost the ball out of bounds. DeCosey's desperation 3 as the shot-clock expired produced a long rebound that Temple's Josh Brown corralled. After a timeout at 20.6 seconds, DeCosey dribbled the time down, then worked his way to the free throw line where he pumped-faked a defender out of the way and swished the winner, keeping Temple's NCAA hopes alive. The Owls (18-10, 12-4 American), who got 18 points from Obi Enechionyia, are a half-game ahead of SMU, which plays Sunday, atop the league standings. Walker had 21 points and Tacko Fall had 13 points and 14 rebounds for UCF (11-16, 5-11).
